{"descriptions":[{"id":1241,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eTibetan contains an important set of epistemic stative verbs (or copulas). These do not vary in relation to tense-aspect. As in the case of declarative stative verbs, a distinction is drawn between existential and essential copulas. The former are derived from the verb \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡོད་\u003c/span\u003e and the latter from the verb \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡིན་\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe existential copulas and their negatives are:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ctable border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"58\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡོད་པ་འདྲ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"69\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡོད་ཀྱི་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"70\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡོད་ས་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"58\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམེད་པ་འདྲ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"69\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡོད་ཀྱི་མ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"70\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡོད་ས་མ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe essential copulas and their negatives are:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ctable border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"48\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡིན་པ་འདྲ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"48\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡིན་ཀྱི་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"48\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡིན་ས་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"48\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམིན་པ་འདྲ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"48\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡིན་ཀྱི་མ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"48\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡིན་ས་མ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThese copulas express a high degree of probability and according to the context may be translated by the use of adverbs such as \u0026ldquo;surely,\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;probably,\u0026rdquo; or the modal verb \u0026ldquo;must.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམི་མང་པོ་ཡོད་པ་འདྲ།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;There must be a lot of people.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའབྲོག་པ་ཡོད་ཀྱི་རེད།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;There must be some nomads.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཁོང་རྒྱ་མི་ཡིན་གྱི་རེད།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;He must be Chinese.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThere is a slight difference between the auxiliaries formed with \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདྲ་\u003c/span\u003e and those formed with \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརེད་\u003c/span\u003e. The former suggests that the speaker\u0026rsquo;s inference is based on his direct observation of the evidence, while the latter indicates that the speaker\u0026rsquo;s inference is based on logic or on factual information not borne out by observation.\u003c/p\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:19 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:19 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}